Defendant Daniel J Berezinski in court with attorney Marcella De Peters.  Defendant Daniel J Berezinski in custody.  
Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
COUNT 1:  

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS with credit for 85 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  
The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 18 MONTHS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (if revoked):
*Obtain AODA and Mental health assessments and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Cooperate with any counseling programs deemed appropriate by agent;
*No contact with Citgo located at 1715 10th Avenue, South Milwaukee;
*Obtain/maintain employment;
*Perform 60 hours of community service at non-profit agency;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

Defendant is informed  may not possess any firearms.
Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  The Court instructs defense counsel to advise the defendant of determinate sentence and appeal rights. 
